Global investors bought a net 2.22
billion rupees ($50 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, rose 2.3 percent to 937.1 billion rupees, or 35
percent of the gross market position, according to the
exchangeâ€™s website. Open interest reached a record 1.6 trillion
rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 6 billion rupees of shares in the
 cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given by
